<p>which is also used as communication depot. (telephones etc) while here several enemy shells landed in the town of Albert, near the railway which is in present use. News rec'd of 1st Div. success the previous night. Concert.</p>
<p>24th. Monday.<br/>Up at 6am no parades during morning, bayonet instruction after lunch</p>
<p>Packs branded &amp; dumped ready for storage till we come out again. About 8pm. we moved off for reserve position &amp; had most tiring advance not knowing just where we were required apparently &amp; about midnight</p>
